HEADWORD: Alto-cumulus
<hw>Al`to-cu"mu*lus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>altus</ets> high + L. & E. <ets>cumulus</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Meteor.)</fld> <def>A fleecy cloud formation consisting of large
whitish or grayish globular cloudlets with shaded portions, often
grouped in flocks or rows.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

